Side of Serra de Caldaz (a flat-topped batholithis dome), 13 km due WSW of city of Caldas Novas. Undisturbed cerradao xeromorphic tree woodland with 40% tree crown covr, on lower part of slope. (this is a transition belt, here 40m wide, between gallery forest lower downslope and open scrub cerrado further upslope). Trees include Copaifera, Aspidosperma, Hymenaea, Pterodon, Machaeriu, Plathymenium, Peltogyne, Wunderlichlia. Many weathered quartizite rocks outcropping slightly in humusy soil.
